questions.Group: Group of the respondent [MCQ: A. Senior B. Junior C. Middle D. Intern]
questions.Frequent_Usage: I think that I would like to use this system frequently. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.System_Complexity: I found the system unnecessarily complex. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Ease_of_Use: I thought the system was easy to use. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Need_for_Technical_Support: I think that I would need the support of a technical person to be able to use this system. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Integration_of_Functions: I found the various functions in this system were well integrated. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Inconsistency: I thought there was too much inconsistency in this system. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Ease_of_Learning: I would imagine that most people would learn to use this system very quickly. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Cumbersome_to_Use: I found the system very awkward to use. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Confidence_in_Use: I felt very confident using the system. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
questions.Need_to_Learn_Before_Use: I needed to learn a lot of things before I could get going with this system. [Likert 1–5: 1 = Strongly Disagree, 5 = Strongly Agree]
